## 🔴 Bugs Found (code doesn't match report OR is broken)

### Bug 1: `web_controller.py` Line 1934 — `RecyclingItem.condition` doesn't exist

```python
# Line 1934-1940 (Section 10: Bottle Condition Breakdown)
cond_base = db.session.query(
    RecyclingItem.condition,          # ← DOES NOT EXIST
    func.count(RecyclingItem.id).label('count'),
).join(RecyclingSession)
```

> [!CAUTION]
> `RecyclingItem` has no `condition` column. The old schema had `condition` (With Label / No Label). The new schema uses `status` (Accepted / Rejected) and `detected_class`. This analytics query will crash at runtime.

**Fix:** Replace `RecyclingItem.condition` with `RecyclingItem.status` (or remove section entirely — it's now redundant with the Accepted/Rejected breakdown in section 1).

---

### Bug 2: `web_controller.py` Line 1949 — `Account` reference still present

```python
# Line 1949 (Section 11: Summary Totals)
total_users_base = db.session.query(func.count(User.id)).join(Account).join(CommunityGroup)
```

> [!CAUTION]
> `Account` model was removed. This will crash with `NameError: name 'Account' is not defined` (it's not imported). Should be `User.query.join(CommunityGroup)`.

---

### Bug 3: `web_controller.py` Lines 2735-2751 — `get_login_history()` uses removed models/fields

```python
# Lines 2738-2744
).join(
    Account, User.account_id == Account.id        # ← Account removed
).join(
    CommunityGroup, Account.community_group_id == CommunityGroup.id  # ← Account removed
).filter(
    ...
).order_by(AdminLog.timestamp.desc())             # ← field is created_at, not timestamp
```

And line 2751:
```python
'timestamp': _dt(l.timestamp),                    # ← field is created_at
```

> [!CAUTION]
> Three issues in one route:
> 1. `Account` model referenced (removed)
> 2. `User.account_id` referenced (removed)  
> 3. `AdminLog.timestamp` referenced (renamed to `created_at`)

