| # | Report Says | Actual Code | Impact |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Report line count: `models.py` — 591 lines | ✅ Matches (591 lines) | None |
| 2 | Report line count: `web_controller.py` — ~2758 lines | Actual: 2757 lines | Negligible |
| 3 | Report says `UserSecurity.two_fa_enabled` | Code uses `two_factor_enabled` (line 267) | Report field name wrong; code is correct |
| 4 | Report § "Next Steps" says `BulkDeposit` model missing | `BulkDeposit` EXISTS at line 470 of `models.py` | Report is stale — this was already fixed |
| 5 | Report § auth_controller row: `GET /me` returns `walletId` | `_serialize_auth_user()` does NOT return `walletId` — it returns `pointsBalance`, `lifetimePoints`, `streak` but no `walletId` key | Minor omission in auth serializer |
| 6 | Report § auth_controller row: `POST /verify-2fa` | Route is actually `POST /verify-otp` (line 271) | Route name mismatch in report |
| 7 | `web_controller.py` line 774: references `name` variable (undefined) | Should be `user.name` — will throw `NameError` at runtime | **Bug** (but in a rarely-hit path) |

